headline: Here's How Many Shares of Domino's Pizza You'd Need to Own to Get $1,000 in Yearly Dividends
summary: How many shares of Domino's Pizza would you need to own to receive $1,000 in annual dividends?  Known for its reasonable prices, convenient locations, and fast delivery, Domino's has continued to open new restaurants at a reasonable pace despite its already massive footprint.  If you're looking primarily for a stock that will provide you with a reliable income stream, you can find higher dividend yields than Domino's 1.3%.

headline: 3 Things to Know About Domino's Pizza Stock Before You Buy
summary: Domino's (NYSE: DPZ) stock found its way back onto many investors' radars last month after Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway disclosed that it had added the pizza purveyor to its portfolio.  News that Buffett is buying any stock tends to put a bright spotlight on it, and that attention can sometimes drive the share price higher.
